						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Śivayōganāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year: lost</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record that Sembiyaṉ Mahādēvi, the mother of Parakēsarivarman <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śrī-Gaṇḍarāditta Madhurāntakadēvar, donated several ornaments to Tiruviśalūr Paramasvāmi, after having the sacred bath of the God performed.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. III No. 148. </p>						

						</summary>
